## Example Violation

**Trigger:** Generated `PostJournalEntryCommandHandler` updates
`JournalEntry.Status` from `DRAFT` to `POSTED` via `_context.Update(entry)`
with no domain event raised and no audit table write.

**What gets flagged:**
> This handler mutates `JournalEntry.Status`, an audit-required field per
> `businessRules.md`, with no audit trail capture. This is the exact failure
> mode behind RHODES's prior stuck-DRAFT-state investigations — without a
> recorded who/when/old-status/new-status, a stuck entry can't be
> distinguished from one mid-transition during incident response. Generate
> a `JournalEntryStatusChanged` domain event, raise it in this handler, and
> add a `JournalEntryStatusChangedHandler` that writes the audit row before
> refusing to proceed — see `pattern-finder` for the established pattern.
